The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Rs 600, Landmark)This concert on the Irish castle grounds packs in unforgettable live performances of U2 classics, the high point of which is a brilliant take on Desire. Catch Bono?s soft underbelly on display in moving tributes to his home-turf fans and family, just a few months after his father?s demise. The Edge, here, is on fire too. 

 THE DISPLAY

 (CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm, from 3 pm on Mondays, May 11 onwards)

 The showcase features works by Paresh Maity, M.F. Husain, Jogen Chowdhury, Somnath Hore, Bikash Bhattacharjee, Ganesh Pyne, Hiran Mitra, Shakila, Paritosh Sen and T. Vaikuntam, among others.

 THE PLAY

 (Kala Mandir, 6 pm, May 8)

 Starring TV star Shweta Kawatra , the Mumbai production is a ribtickling comedy of errors involving a young bachelor and the misundertsandings with his rich but miserly uncle.




